This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on the segmentation of brain tumors in MRI images using deep learning methods. The paper also proposes modifications to the 3D UNet architecture, which is a popular deep learning architecture for image segmentation tasks. 

The paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it uses deep learning methods for the segmentation task. 

The Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper proposes an automatic approach for brain tumor segmentation, which is a task that requires intelligence. 

The Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category is another possibility as the paper uses neural networks for the segmentation task. 

Finally, the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category is a possibility as the paper deals with the analysis of 3D MRI images, which can be considered as a form of multimedia data.
